iter64 (2026-05-27, 0.1.592): CORRECTED a user-flagged live deviation - the agent using the platform Explore subagent (or Task/grep) for code search instead of the gm codesearch spool verb. Root cause: plan.rs named codesearch for ORIENT but NOTHING forbade the platform Explore agent for ad-hoc EXECUTE searches, and SKILL.md had ZERO mention of it - so an agent whose platform offers Explore reaches for it, bypassing the spool + the committed code-search index + the recall-grounded discipline (same class as forbidden puppeteer-vs-browser). FIX (both surfaces): SKILL.md (always-loaded) gained a Search-routes-through-spool rule (codesearch verb only; Explore/Task/grep/host-native NOT substitutes); execute.rs (rs-plugkit ece60b1) gained the matching EXECUTE-phase directive. LESSON: for every plugkit capability that has a platform-native equivalent (browser, search, exec), the skill must EXPLICITLY forbid the native tool and name the verb - an implicit preference is not enough; agents default to their platform tools unless told otherwise. Also assessed the iter63 lora namespace-train: meaningful only with multiple enabled disciplines (enabled.txt empty=default-only now), sequenced as next refinement.